    <title>The seL4 Summit 2026 Keynotes and &quot;Voices from Nearby&quot;</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://sel4.systems/news/2026.html"/>
    <id>https://sel4.systems/news/2026.html</id>
    <published>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</published>
    <updated>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</updated>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;h3&gt;Keynotes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  We are pleased to announce that we have two outstanding keynotes for the &lt;a
  href=&quot;/Summit/2026/&quot;&gt;seL4 Summit 2026&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/anjanarajan/&quot;&gt;Anjana
  Rajan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, Former Assistant National Cyber Director at The White
  House, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/mpdehnel/&quot;&gt;Martin
  Dehnel-Wild&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, Chief Scientist
  at Kry10. Abstracts coming soon — stay tuned!
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;grid grid-rows-1 w-2/3 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-10 mt-5&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      &lt;img src=&quot;../images/summit/anjana-square.jpg&quot; class=&quot;rounded-xl w-full
      ml-1 mt-0&quot; alt=&quot;Photo of Anjana Rajan&quot;&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/anjanarajan/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anjana
      Rajan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Former Assistant National Cyber Director at The
      White House.
    &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      &lt;img src=&quot;../images/summit/martin-square.jpg&quot; class=&quot;float-right
      rounded-xl w-full ml-1 mt-0&quot; alt=&quot;Photo of Martin Dehnel-Wild&quot;&gt;
      &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/mpdehnel/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Martin
      Dehnel-Wild&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Chief Scientist at Kry10.
    &lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&quot;Voices from Nearby&quot;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  This year, the summit will feature a full first day dedicated to applications,
  overviews, and perspectives on seL4-based systems and formally verified
  software in the real world. This will include a session on &quot;Voices from
  Nearby,&quot; with industry experts who work in or share their thoughts on
  areas that are adjacent to the core seL4 areas. &lt;a
  href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/in/alistair-woodman-51934433/&quot;&gt;Alistair
  Woodmand&lt;/a&gt;, Board Member of the Erlang Ecosystem Foundation, will share
